two-year struggle to find a suitable tribute for the slain civil rights leader 
in San Diego. ; Photo, Newly installed sign on California 94 proclaims that it 
is now the Martin Luther King Jr. Freeway. DON BARTLETTI / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
